cs.IT, cs.EM, cs.SY, cs.NI, cs.MM

Reasoning: 
1. cs.IT (Information Theory): The paper deals with the optimization of the transmit waveform to maximize the harvested power at the receiver, which involves the manipulation of information-bearing signals. 
2. cs.EM (Electromagnetics): The paper focuses on the design of a single-input single-output (SISO) radio-frequency (RF) wireless power transfer (WPT) system, which involves the study of electromagnetic fields and their interactions with the environment. 
3. cs.SY (Systems and Control): The paper proposes two suboptimal solutions to the non-convex waveform design problem, which involves the application of control theory and optimization techniques. 
4. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture): The paper deals with the wireless power transfer problem, which is a key issue in the development of wireless networks and the Internet of Things (IoT). 
5. cs.MM (Multimedia): The paper uses simulations to demonstrate the performance gain of the proposed waveform designs, which involves the processing and analysis of multimedia data.
